The paper discusses the modeling and simulation of distributed resource management and scheduling for grid computing, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the use of peer-to-peer networks, which could fall under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The development of a Java-based toolkit for simulation suggests a focus on Software Engineering (cs.SE). The use of discrete-event simulation could also suggest a focus on Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the evaluation of scheduling algorithms could suggest a focus on Systems and Control (cs.SY).
